are my thoughts it feels like i left him there to die said 
ruthie alqallef a memphis tenn native l feel like i 
deserted him 
she and hundreds of other american wives and children who fled 
the middle east remain trapped by visions of loved ones left 
behind 
leaving him was the hardest thing ive ever done said mrs 
alqallef whose husband of 10 years is a kuwaiti military officer 
his face scared me more than the whole six weeks we spent in 
hiding 
her husbands eyes were glazed his expression frozen his 
silence didnt add to the tension she said it was the tension 
he didnt know how to say goodbye 
separated families were the result of saddam husseins order 
that foreign men not be allowed to leave after his invasion of 
kuwait in early august many are being used as shields against 
attack 
an estimated 930 americans remain in kuwait and 170 in iraq the 
state department says at the time of the invasion about 3500 
