east 
the windows at our house were covered we couldnt answer the 
door or the telephone the kids had to stay indoors and it was 
so hot mrs knutson said in a telephone interview last week from 
minneapolis 
you couldnt find chicken eggs bread i heard the medical 
supplies were getting low too she said i just kept thinking 
i have to get my children out of here i knew i had to leave my 
husband 
now she like the other displaced mothers is thinking about how 
to make ends meet they are looking for jobs getting their kids 
into school pushing back frightening thoughts of their husbands 
for the sake of their kids 
at night we all sleep together the kids and me theyre 
wonderful but so little its not like snuggling up against your 
big husband said mrs alqallef i want my husband back 
