<TEXT>
patriarch alexi ii head of the russian orthodox 
church led a divine liturgy in the kremlins uspensky cathedral on 
sunday the first full service allowed in more than 70 years in 
russias most important cathedral 
before the 1917 revolution the 15th century church was the most 
sacred in the country under its five golden onionshaped domes 
czars were crowned patriarchs were buried and conquered princes 
swore allegiance to russia 
since 1918 however it has been a museum and closed to ordinary 
worship the governments decision to allow the sunday service was 
an important symbolic step in the revival of the orthodox church 
long repressed by the communist party because of ideological 
opposition to religion 
about 1000 people were allowed into the kremlin the walled 
fortress that is the seat of the soviet government for the 
service 
among them were moscow mayor gavriil popov and the chairman of 
the national legislature anatoly lukyanov 
afterward thousands of people lined the streets as alexi and 
other church leaders led a procession from the kremlins trinity 
gate through downtown moscow to another historic site the church 
of the great ascension 
churches are revived not by external restoration but by 
prayers said inside them alexi told the crowd outside i hope 
you will agree with me that todays divine liturgy in the uspensky 
ctahedral meant more to its spiritual revival than decades of 
external maintenance 
more than 30 clergymen in golden brocade robes many carrying 
icons took part in the hourlong procession they were followed by 
hundreds of worshipers 
people watched from balconies and windows and were packed four 
deep on both sides of the 2mile route the crowd was quiet and 
respectful and some spectators crossed themselves as the icons 
paintings of the virgin and various saints passed by 
we are russians god is with us said a banner in old 
russian script carried by some of the marchers 
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev has shown much more 
tolerance than previous leaders for worshipers and has called on 
them to support his reform policies 
three years ago gorbachev met in the kremlin with alexis 
predecessor pimen it was the first meeting between leaders of the 
communist party and the russian orthodox church in more than 40 
years 
since then numerous churches across the soviet union have been 
returned to the orthodox church and restored for worship in prior 
decades some were maintained as cultural museums but many were 
allowed to fall into disrepair and were used as storehouses or 
offices 
since the bolshevik revolution brief prayer services have been 
allowed in the uspensky cathedral on a few occasions such as in 
