<TEXT>
the government warned sunday of a worldwide 
surge in antisemitic violence and said attitudes toward jews were 
slipping back to the spirit of the 19th century 
a 12page report reviewing antisemitism in 1990 cited murders 
and bombings among the incidents 
it said the soviet union and eastern europe were the focal 
points of attacks and threats against jews by ultra rightwing 
activists operating more freely since democratic reforms 
also blamed for growing antijewish sentiments were neonazis 
moslem fundamentalists and christian groups mostly in western 
europe 
social upheavals in some countries also have turned jews again 
into scapegoats the report said 
in latin america for example jews are increasingly targeted 
by terrorist groups especially leftist ones in their war against 
their governments it said 
antisemitism also is on the rise in the united states and 
canada the report said 
it said that desecrations of jewish cemeteries such as in 
carpentras france last may had reached epidemic proportions in 
many nations 
the conclusion without trying to create panic is a feeling 
that open antisemitism is growing with many countries sliding into 
tolerance a normalization that is in the spirit of the 19th 
century despite all the jewish people went through in the 20th 
century the report said 
cabinet secretary eliakim rubinstein who compiled the report 
suggested in an interview on israeli radio that more could be done 
by authorities in other nations to quell antisemitic acts 
there are two weapons to use one is by warning putting 
perpetrators on trial the second is through education like 
making the holocaust not only a marginal chapter in history 
classes rubinstein said 
an estimated 6 million jews died at the hands of the nazis 
during world war ii the holocaust was a catalyst for the founding 
of israel in 1948 
rubinsteins committee began studying antisemitism in 1988 
sundays report was its third and most severe 
it cited 18 antisemitic attacks on jews including bombings 
kidnappings and beatings so far this year 
three attacks were in western europe including britain two in 
the united states two in south africa one in new zealand and 10 
in latin america including several kidnappings murders and 
bombings the report said it gave no details 
in the soviet union the report claims ultranationalist groups 
have blamed jews for corruption and the downfall of communism 
much of the soviet antisemitism has surfaced in criticisms in 
prominent newspapers and threats of pogroms organized attacks used 
against jews in czarist russia the report said 
a report by the quasigovernment jewish agency predicted up to 2 
million soviet jews could emigrate to israel by 1995 swelling the 
nations present population of 45 million by 45 percent some of 
the immigration is prompted by an antisemitic atmosphere the 
agencys report said 
on the popular level you didnt see as much antisemitism 
before glasnost because there was more government control 
rubinstein said 
the report said soviet president mikhail gorbachev had failed to 
publicly condemn the antisemitism perhaps because of his 
attempts to maintain the support of various conservative 
elements 
