cuban missile crisis 
khrushchev who was ousted from power in the soviet union in 
1964 and who died in 1971 also thanked julius and ethel rosenberg 
for helping the soviet union develop the atomic bomb 
khrushchev made a series of tapes as he lived out his last seven 
years under virtual house arrest in the village of petrovodalneye 
on the outskirts of moscow many of the tapes were smuggled to the 
west and two volumes of memoirs khrushchev remembers and 
khrushchev remembers the last testament were published in the 
1970s 
